gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAINS NATIONAL PARK

Plants of Tennessee

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee: Sevier County
35.6874° Latitude -83.5042° Longitude 2000 Feet Elevation
Quadrangle: Gatlinburg Le Conte Watershed
T. 10S, R. 72E, Sect. 20

The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. 1.9 mile south by southeast of Gatlinburg, Tennessee. Along Le Conte Creek just below the Twin Creeks Uplands Research Lab. Coordinate Datum: WGS84/NAD83. Northeast-facing (45°) steep wooded slope about 100+ feet above Le Conte Creek. Growing with *Quercus prinus*, *Tsuga canadensis* (dead), *Galax urceolata*, *Leucothoe fontanesiana*, *Medeola virginiana*, etc. Evergreen perennial herb with white flowers.

42765 Loy R. Phillippe, Grant Cunningham, Jenny Stratton, and Valerie Sivicek
30 May 2011

Illinois Natural History Survey (ILLS)

SERNEC Digitization Project - Tennessee Herbarium Consortium

GSMNP10730 (Handwritten)
GRSM 161857 (Handwritten)


*Galax urceolata*
